		<header class="entry-header">
			<section class="kicker">Future Facing</section>
						<a href="http://betaboston.com/news/2014/08/11/real-life-analytics-will-watch-your-face-while-you-shop/" rel="bookmark" class="entry-link" title="Real Life Analytics will watch your face while you shop">
																			<section class="headline "><span>Real Life Analytics will watch your face while you shop</span></section>
										<section class="media"><img width="466" height="268" src="http://betaboston.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/realLife-founders.jpg" class="attachment-teaser wp-post-image" alt="realLife-founders" /></section>
											</a>
						<section class="post-info">
		<div class="social">
		<a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=Real Life Analytics will watch your face while you shop&url=http%3A%2F%2Fbetaboston.com%2Fnews%2F2014%2F08%2F11%2Freal-life-analytics-will-watch-your-face-while-you-shop%2F&related=BetaBoston&via=BetaBoston" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="share-twi btn" alt="Share on Twitter"></a>
	<a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbetaboston.com%2Fnews%2F2014%2F08%2F11%2Freal-life-analytics-will-watch-your-face-while-you-shop%2F" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="share-fb btn" alt="Share on Facebook"></a>
					<a href="http://betaboston.com/news/2014/08/11/real-life-analytics-will-watch-your-face-while-you-shop/#comments" class="more-link btn comment-count" title="0 Comments">0</a>
	</div>		<div class="author">
			<a href="http://betaboston.com/author/nidhi/" rel="author" class="profile-link">
				<span class="pic"><img src="http://betaboston.com/wp-content/uploads/userphoto/86.thumbnail.jpg" alt="Nidhi Subbaraman" class="photo" width="27" height="27" /></span>
				<span class="name">Nidhi Subbaraman</span>
			</a>
							<a class="twi-link" href="https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=NidhiSubs">@NidhiSubs</a>
					</div>
		<div class="timestamp">
			<time class="updated" title="08/11/2014 10:22:52" pubdate>08/11/2014</time>
		</div>
	</section>
</header>	<section class="entry-content">
		The trio behind Real Life Analytics is aiming for a Minority Report future. The MassChallenge finalists are building a system that will help retailers watch customers entering their stores and eventually serve them ads based on their age, race, and gender, sort of like the personalized treatment Tom Cruise’s character gets at the GAP.

 <a href="http://betaboston.com/news/2014/08/11/real-life-analytics-will-watch-your-face-while-you-shop/#more-15206" class="more-link">Read More</a>
	</section>
	<footer class="entry-footer">
