</article><article id="post-13659" class="teaser" role="article">
		<header class="entry-header">
			<section class="kicker">Servers Logged</section>
						<a href="http://betaboston.com/news/2014/07/03/nsas-xkeyscore-program-targeted-visitors-to-mit-server-tor-project-for-enhanced-scrutiny/" rel="bookmark" class="entry-link" title="NSA's Xkeyscore program targeted visitors to MIT server, Tor Project for enhanced scrutiny">
																			<section class="headline "><span>NSA's Xkeyscore program targeted visitors to MIT server, Tor Project for enhanced scrutiny</span></section>
										<section class="media"><img width="466" height="262" src="http://betaboston.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Tor-Privacy-Womens-Shelter.jpg" class="attachment-teaser wp-post-image" alt="Tor-Privacy-Womens-Shelter" /></section>
											</a>
						<section class="post-info">
		<div class="social">
		<a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=NSA&#8217;s Xkeyscore program targeted visitors to MIT server, Tor Project for enhanced scrutiny&url=http%3A%2F%2Fbetaboston.com%2Fnews%2F2014%2F07%2F03%2Fnsas-xkeyscore-program-targeted-visitors-to-mit-server-tor-project-for-enhanced-scrutiny%2F&related=BetaBoston&via=BetaBoston" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="share-twi btn" alt="Share on Twitter"></a>
	<a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbetaboston.com%2Fnews%2F2014%2F07%2F03%2Fnsas-xkeyscore-program-targeted-visitors-to-mit-server-tor-project-for-enhanced-scrutiny%2F" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="share-fb btn" alt="Share on Facebook"></a>
					<a href="http://betaboston.com/news/2014/07/03/nsas-xkeyscore-program-targeted-visitors-to-mit-server-tor-project-for-enhanced-scrutiny/#comments" class="more-link btn comment-count" title="0 Comments">0</a>
	</div>		<div class="author">
			<a href="http://betaboston.com/author/morisy/" rel="author" class="profile-link">
				<span class="pic"><img src="http://betaboston.com/wp-content/uploads/userphoto/3.thumbnail.jpg" alt="Michael Morisy" class="photo" width="27" height="27" /></span>
				<span class="name">Michael Morisy</span>
			</a>
							<a class="twi-link" href="https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=morisy">@morisy</a>
					</div>
		<div class="timestamp">
			<time class="updated" title="07/03/2014 22:26:42" pubdate>07/03/2014</time>
		</div>
	</section>
</header>	<section class="entry-content">
		A new report from noted security researchers — first <a href="http://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/aktuell/nsa230_page-4.html">published in conjunction with German news program Tagesschau</a> — states that the NSA's Xkeyscore program, which determines who is flagged for enhanced tracking and monitoring, targeted every visitor to a particular MIT server, visitors seeking information on the privacy-focused Tor Project, which is based in Cambridge, and those who simply searched for information on the privacy-enhanced TAILS operating system.

 <a href="http://betaboston.com/news/2014/07/03/nsas-xkeyscore-program-targeted-visitors-to-mit-server-tor-project-for-enhanced-scrutiny/#more-13659" class="more-link">Read More</a>
	</section>
